quests.desc: You are now playing a exciting game of TextWorld! Here is how to play! First stop, ensure that the chest drawer within the bedroom is open. Once you have opened the chest drawer, recover the old key from the chest drawer in the bedroom. After getting the old key, unlock the wooden door in the bedroom. And then, open the wooden door. Once you have pulled open the wooden door, go east. And once you've done that, you win!
commands: take old key from chest drawer
unlock wooden door with old key

infos.name: kitchen
infos.desc:
Well how about that, you are in the place we're calling the kitchen.

 [if c_2 is locked]A locked[else if c_2 is open]An open[otherwise]A closed[end if] refrigerator is right there by you.[if c_2 is open and there is something in the c_2] The refrigerator contains [a list of things in the c_2].[end if][if c_2 is open and the c_2 contains nothing] The refrigerator is empty, what a horrible day![end if] You can make out a counter. The counter is ordinary.[if there is something on the s_1] On the counter you see [a list of things on the s_1].[end if][if there is nothing on the s_1] But the thing is empty.[end if] You can make out a stove. [if there is something on the s_2]You see [a list of things on the s_2] on the stove.[end if][if there is nothing on the s_2]But oh no! there's nothing on this piece of garbage.[end if] You can see a kitchen island. Make a note of this, you might have to put stuff on or in it later on. [if there is something on the s_3]On the kitchen island you can see [a list of things on the s_3].[end if][if there is nothing on the s_3]But the thing is empty. Hopefully this doesn't make you too upset.[end if]

 There is [if d_1 is open]an open[otherwise]a closed[end if] screen door leading east. There is [if d_0 is open]an open[otherwise]a closed[end if] wooden door leading west. There is an unguarded exit to the north. You need an unguarded exit? You should try going south.

infos.name: bedroom
infos.desc:
Well, here we are in the bedroom.

 [if c_0 is locked]A locked[else if c_0 is open]An open[otherwise]A closed[end if] chest drawer is right there by you.[if c_0 is open and there is something in the c_0] The chest drawer contains [a list of things in the c_0].[end if][if c_0 is open and the c_0 contains nothing] The chest drawer is empty! This is the worst thing that could possibly happen, ever![end if] You make out an antique trunk.[if c_1 is open and there is something in the c_1] The antique trunk contains [a list of things in the c_1].[end if][if c_1 is open and the c_1 contains nothing] Empty! What kind of nightmare TextWorld is this?[end if] You make out a king-size bed. You shudder, but continue examining the king-size bed. The king-size bed is standard.[if there is something on the s_0] On the king-size bed you can make out [a list of things on the s_0].[end if][if there is nothing on the s_0] But oh no! there's nothing on this piece of garbage. It would have been so cool if there was stuff on the king-size bed.[end if]

 There is [if d_0 is open]an open[otherwise]a closed[end if] wooden door leading east.

infos.name: backyard
infos.desc:
You've entered a backyard.

 Look out! It's a- oh, never mind, it's just a set of chairs. You shudder, but continue examining the set of chairs. [if there is something on the s_10]You see [a list of things on the s_10] on the set of chairs.[end if][if there is nothing on the s_10]Unfortunately, there isn't a thing on it. Hm. Oh well[end if] You can see a bbq. You wonder idly who left that here. [if there is something on the s_8]You see [a list of things on the s_8] on the bbq.[end if][if there is nothing on the s_8]Unfortunately, there isn't a thing on it.[end if] You can make out a patio table. Now why would someone leave that there? The patio table is ordinary.[if there is something on the s_9] On the patio table you can make out [a list of things on the s_9]. You idly wonder how they came up with the name TextWorld for this place. It's pretty fitting.[end if][if there is nothing on the s_9] However, the patio table, like an empty patio table, has nothing on it. What, you think everything in TextWorld should have stuff on it?[end if]

 There is [if d_1 is open]an open[otherwise]a closed[end if] screen door leading west. You don't like doors? Why not try going south, that entranceway is unguarded.

infos.name: living room
infos.desc:
You arrive in a living room. An usual kind of place. You begin to take stock of what's here.

 You make out a couch. [if there is something on the s_5]You see [a list of things on the s_5] on the couch.[end if][if there is nothing on the s_5]However, the couch, like an empty couch, has nothing on it. Aw, and here you were, all excited for there to be things on it![end if] You can see a low table. [if there is something on the s_6]You see [a list of things on the s_6] on the low table.[end if][if there is nothing on the s_6]However, the low table, like an empty low table, has nothing on it. Oh! Why couldn't there just be stuff on it?[end if] You scan the room for a tv, and you find a tv. The tv is standard.[if there is something on the s_7] On the tv you make out [a list of things on the s_7].[end if][if there is nothing on the s_7] But oh no! there's nothing on this piece of garbage. What, you think everything in TextWorld should have stuff on it?[end if]

You need an unguarded exit? You should try going north.

infos.name: bathroom
infos.desc:
You've stumbled into an ordinary room. Your mind races to think of what kind of room would be ordinary. And then it hits you. Of course. You're in the bathroom. You begin to take stock of what's here.

 You can make out [if c_3 is locked]a locked[else if c_3 is open]an opened[otherwise]a closed[end if] toilet here.[if c_3 is open and there is something in the c_3] The toilet contains [a list of things in the c_3].[end if][if c_3 is open and the c_3 contains nothing] The toilet is empty! What a waste of a day![end if] You see [if c_4 is locked]a locked[else if c_4 is open]an opened[otherwise]a closed[end if] bath.[if c_4 is open and there is something in the c_4] The bath contains [a list of things in the c_4].[end if][if c_4 is open and the c_4 contains nothing] The bath is empty, what a horrible day![end if] You see a sink. [if there is something on the s_4]You see [a list of things on the s_4] on the sink. Wow! Just like in the movies![end if][if there is nothing on the s_4]The sink appears to be empty. Oh! Why couldn't there just be stuff on it?[end if]

There is an exit to the south. Don't worry, it is unguarded.
